    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In general, Graph Neural Networks (GNN) refer to the general concept of applying neural networks (NNs) on graphs. In a <a href="https://medium.com/graph-convolutional-networks-gcn-pooling-839184205692" target="_self">previous</a> article, we cover GCN which is one of the popular approaches in GNN. But in some literature, GNN may refer to a more specific approach that the hidden state of a node depends on its last states and its neighbors. We can view this as message passings with its neighboring nodes. Mathematically, it has the form of:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
