    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Now, we have finished our discussion on the original GNN models. Let’s broaden our view and look at other generic GNN models.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">Graph autoencoders (GAEs)</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">GAE is the cousin of autoencoder in deep learning.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/700/0*5tt6mmr7je6qF6mg.jpg"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">Autoencoder</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It encodes a graph into a latent feature space and reconstructs the graph from it. First, the encoder applies graph convolutional layers to generate a <strong>network embedding</strong> for each node. We train the model such that this representation will capture the topological information of a node. Next, the decoder computes the pair-wise similarity between network embeddings followed by an activation function. Finally, the decoder reconstructs the graph adjacency matrix using this calculation. GAE is trained to minimize the reconstruction loss between the real adjacency matrix and the decoded adjacency matrix.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
