    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">ST-GCN proposes three partition strategies in dividing and grouping the neighbors of a root node (central node): (b) Uni-labeling, (c) distance partitioning, and (d) spatial configuration partition. In each partition scheme, it assigns labels to nodes systematically and uses these labels to associate the weights (or to calculate the weights) in a consistent manner.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
