    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In uni-labeling partitioning, all nodes have the same label (green). In Distance partitioning, there are two labels — the root node itself with distance 0 (green) and other neighboring points with distance 1. (blue). In Spatial configuration partitioning (d), nodes are labeled according to their distances to the skeleton gravity center (black cross) compared with that of the root node. Centripetal nodes are closer to the black cross than the center node and mark as blue while centrifugal nodes are further away and mark as yellow.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In the distance partition, it labels a node with <em>l </em>measures its node distance from the center node. In our case, it is either 0 or 1 since we consider the immediate neighbors only.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
